This brings us to the interval after the Garden Act , with the strange conduct observed by M. Remy and those curious lapses from the dignity that might be expected of the managers . 
Giry was to slip the twenty thousand francs . 
M. Richard went and placed himself at the identical spot where he had stood when he bowed to the under secretary for fine arts . 
M. Moncharmin took up his position a few steps behind him . 
