Then come stage upholsterers , whose sole duty is to lay carpets , hang curtains , etc . 
gas men , and a squad of firemen . 
Claqueurs , call boys , property men , dressers , coiffeurs , supernumeraries , and artists , follow . 
There are about a hundred choristers , and about eighty musicians . 
This personnel is provided for as follows Eighty dressing rooms are reserved for the artists , each including a small antechamber , the dressing room proper , and a little closet . 
A few figures taken from the article will suggest the enormous capacity and the perfect convenience of the house . 
The musicians have a foyer with closets for their instruments . 
The author remarks of his visit to the Opera House that it was almost as bewildering as it was agreeable . 
Giant stairways and colossal halls , huge frescoes and enormous mirrors , gold and marble , satin and velvet , met the eye at every turn . 
